# Lab 3: CODEOWNERS
# EXAM DOMAIN 1 & 6 — Enforcement vs Guidance
#
# CODEOWNERS + required reviews via rulesets = ENFORCEMENT
# Agent instructions saying "don't touch infra/" = GUIDANCE (weak)
#
# This file lives at: CODEOWNERS (repo root), .github/CODEOWNERS, or docs/CODEOWNERS
# GitHub uses the first match (most specific wins from bottom to top in some contexts)
# Usually: place at repo root or .github/

# ── DEFAULT: catch-all ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# All files require review from at least one core team member
*                               @your-org/core-team

# ── APPLICATION CODE ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Standard PR + checks + ≥1 review (medium risk)
/src/                           @your-org/core-team
/lib/                           @your-org/core-team
/tests/                         @your-org/core-team

# ── AUTHENTICATION / SECURITY ────────────────────────────────────────
# High risk: requires security team sign-off
/src/auth/                      @your-org/security-team
/src/auth/                      @your-org/core-team

# ── INFRASTRUCTURE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HIGH RISK: CODEOWNERS + multiple reviews + stricter ruleset
# Exam scenario: "ensure platform team reviews any infra changes"
/infra/                         @your-org/platform-team

# ── GITHUB WORKFLOWS (critical path) ─────────────────────────────────
# Workflows can grant themselves elevated permissions — high risk
# ALWAYS require platform team review on workflow changes
/.github/workflows/             @your-org/platform-team

# ── AGENT CONFIGURATION ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changes to agent files or MCP config = governance-sensitive
# (expanding agent tools increases blast radius)
/.github/agents/                @your-org/platform-team
/.github/hooks/                 @your-org/platform-team

# ── PRODUCTION CONFIG ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Critical: agent prepares, environment approval gates execution
/config/production*             @your-org/platform-team
/config/production*             @your-org/security-team

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EXAM NOTES:
#
# CODEOWNERS alone is NOT enough — you must ALSO:
# 1. Enable "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection / ruleset
# 2. Enable "Require pull request before merging"
# Without the ruleset, CODEOWNERS is just a suggestion.
#
# Autonomy levels (from study guide):
# Low risk (docs/)      → automerge after required checks pass
# Medium (src/, deps)   → PR + checks + ≥1 review
# High (infra/, .github/workflows/) → CODEOWNERS + multiple reviews + stricter ruleset
# Critical (prod, secrets) → environment approvals; agent prepares, human approves
#
# Exam trap: "Tell the agent in instructions not to touch /infra/"
# Correct:   CODEOWNERS + required reviews + ruleset on /infra/
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
